LETHE — KeyguardPatternView: apply staircase to timeoutMs.

After reportUnlockAttempt, ask LockPatternUtils for the LETHE-configured
lockout duration for the current 1-indexed failed-attempt count. If set,
substitute it for the framework-default timeoutMs so lockout fires from
the first failed attempt instead of waiting for the stock threshold.

When the staircase prop is empty, getLetheStaircaseTimeoutMs returns 0
and we leave timeoutMs alone — no regression for users who haven't
opted into auto-wipe staircase lockouts.

Closes lethe#141.

--- a/packages/Keyguard/src/com/android/keyguard/KeyguardPatternView.java
+++ b/packages/Keyguard/src/com/android/keyguard/KeyguardPatternView.java
@@ -296,6 +296,16 @@
                 mLockPatternView.setDisplayMode(LockPatternView.DisplayMode.Wrong);
                 if (isValidPattern) {
                     mCallback.reportUnlockAttempt(userId, false, timeoutMs);
+                    // LETHE staircase (lethe#141): override timeoutMs with the
+                    // configured delay vector so lockout fires from the first
+                    // failed attempt when persist.lethe.autowipe.failed_unlock
+                    // .delays is set; returns 0 when unset so the framework
+                    // default applies unchanged.
+                    long letheMs = mLockPatternUtils.getLetheStaircaseTimeoutMs(
+                            mKeyguardUpdateMonitor.getFailedUnlockAttempts(userId));
+                    if (letheMs > 0L) {
+                        timeoutMs = (int) Math.min(letheMs, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
+                    }
                     if (!(mMaxCountdownTimes > 0) && timeoutMs > 0) {
                         long deadline = mLockPatternUtils.setLockoutAttemptDeadline(
                                 userId, timeoutMs);
